text: Corey Donoghue (born 15 January 1973) is an English retired footballer who is last known to have played for Oslo-based club Mercantile SFK in Norway in 2001. ==Norway== Donoghue joined Norwegian third-tier club Bærum SK from Sittingbourne ahead of the 1998 season. It was claimed in local media outlets that Donoghue had a background in Wolverhampton Wanderers, and he was a journeyman footballer with Bærum being his tenth club.
